data.text:
Cara Melle is an American drag performer and one of the contestants on the fifth season of RuPaul's Drag Race UK.

Drag Name Origin[]

Her name may be a pun on the food "caramel".

Track Record(s)[]

Cara Melle Seasons Competed: UK Season 5 Ranking: 6th Place Maxi Challenges Won: 1 (Ep. 3) Top 2 Placements: 1 (Ep. 1) Mini Challenges Won: 0 Times as Team Captain: 0 Times in Bottom Two: 2 (Eps. 4, 7) Episode Eliminated: Episode 7

Memorable Quotes[]

RuPaul's Drag Race UK Season 5[]

"Kneel for your goddess." (entrance quote)

"Oh, Pangina, Pangina, Pangina... I'll give you something to cry about!"

"I don't owe you anything, I don't owe you an example. I don't owe you this."

♪ "Sweet, salty, sticky, if you're nasty. I'm your action she-ro, sci-fi fantasy. Miss Melle's a sexy queen, I know misgendering has got to go. Black trans lives matter everyday!" ♪ (Verse in Don't Ick My Yum)

"You get the badge, and then you turn into a bitch." (responding to Ginger Johnson)

"Baby, I love lamb, so let's make some lamb chops... How 'bout that?!"

"I feel half bad, 'cause I think we grew to actually like each other. However, the other half of me is saying, 'Ding dong! The witch is dead.'" (after Banksie's elimination)

"I should've made miss thang be one of the pop divas!" (after Ginger won with the role she wanted)

"I am Dionne Warwick, and you're welcome for my presence!" (as Dionne Warwick in Snatch Game)

"Well, no I'm not. But shall we move on?" (as Dionne Warwick in Snatch Game)

"I've one last thing to say... you're welcome for my presence." (exit quote)

Trivia[]

She is the first queen on RuPaul's Drag Race UK to originate from the United States, originating from Atlanta, Georgia.

She, along with fellow Season 5 contestant Alexis Saint-Pete (Poland) are the fourth pair to originate outside of the UK, following Season 4's Starlet (South Africa), Season 3's Choriza May (Spain), and Season 1's Crystal (Canada).

Cara is the seventh queen born in the United States to compete on an international Drag Race franchise, following Gia Gunn, Kandy Ho, Marie Laveau, and Rochelle Mon Chéri on The Switch Drag Race, Genie on Drag Race Thailand, and Hollywould Star on RuPaul's Drag Race Down Under.

She is the second transgender contestant to compete on RuPaul's Drag Race UK, after Season 4's Dakota Schiffer.

Furthermore, she is the first black transgender contestant to compete on RuPaul’s Drag Race UK.

Her favourite Drag Race contestant is Symone.[5]

Her favourite Drag Race lip-sync is "Shut Up and Drive" from All Stars 2, between Alyssa Edwards and Tatianna.[5]

Cara Melle revealed in Episode 1 of Season 5 that she lives with fellow contestant, Tomara Thomas.

They are the second pair of queens on Drag Race UK to have lived together at the time of filming, after A'Whora and Tayce.

She is the first contestant to win the Drag Race UK Girl Group challenge solo.

On Episode 3, Cara Melle became the first ever contestant to be in the Top 2 twice in a single season without the Top 2 format.

Cara is the first contestant to win and lose both top 2 and bottom 2 lipsyncs in the same season.

Cara Melle was absent in the roast and in the finale.

Crystal Methyd, Cara Melle, Heidi N Closet, and Trinity The Tuck starred in the Tubi movie Slay.[6]

Cara auditioned for every UK Season, US Season 10 and US Season 12.[7]
